A total of 34 representative target sequences (RTSs) were selected for validation of the CNVR determined by the array-CGH analysis and of the regions 62 kb upstream and downstream of the CNVR. For each RTS, a pair of primers (Additional file 1: Table S1) was designed using the Primer 3 web tool (http://bioinfo.ut.ee/primer3-0.4.0/). In addition, the in silico polymerase chain reaction (PCR) program from the University of California Santa Cruz (UCSC) browser (http://genome.ucsc.edu) was used for specificity analysis to certify that the primer pair matched only the sequence of interest. The actin gene was co-amplified with the RTSs and served as an endogenous Ref. [4]. The relative comparative threshold cycle (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
